WEBVTT

00:01.634 --> 00:04.571
<i>[cheerful music]</i>

00:04.637 --> 00:12.379
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:12.445 --> 00:14.681
<i>- ♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:14.748 --> 00:16.416
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:16.483 --> 00:18.752
<i>♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:18.818 --> 00:24.424
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:24.491 --> 00:26.326
<i>♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:26.393 --> 00:29.596
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:31.564 --> 00:32.499
- Hey, Harvey.

00:32.564 --> 00:33.800
{\an1}Check out the inside
of this bag.

00:33.867 --> 00:35.335
{\an3}- Okay.
Here I come.

00:35.402 --> 00:37.871
Whoa!
This is a cool bag.

00:37.937 --> 00:39.873
I love this material!

00:39.939 --> 00:41.908
It's got a nice scent to it.

00:41.975 --> 00:43.610
Kind of musky.

00:43.676 --> 00:45.011
You know what?

00:45.078 --> 00:47.180
{\an3}This would be
a great picnic bag.

00:47.247 --> 00:50.884
{\an3}You could fit so many snacks
in here!

00:50.950 --> 00:54.788
Honestly, coolest thing
I've seen today.

00:54.854 --> 00:56.156
Whoa!

00:56.222 --> 00:58.191
<i>[bluesy rock and roll music]</i>

00:58.258 --> 01:01.394
[bell rings, pool balls clack]

01:01.461 --> 01:03.663
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:03.730 --> 01:05.999
Foo?
- Hey, man.

01:06.065 --> 01:07.534
- Sorry, cool bag,

01:07.600 --> 01:11.070
but this is the coolest thing
I've seen today.

01:11.137 --> 01:18.278
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:21.147 --> 01:23.316
- Hey, Boss.
Got some new meat.

01:23.383 --> 01:25.885
{\an3}- Hi, Mr. Boss Sir!
I'm Harvey Beaks.

01:25.952 --> 01:28.955
- I know who you are, kid.

01:29.022 --> 01:30.457
- [gasps] Blister!

01:30.523 --> 01:32.859
{\an3}I really like your little club,
Blister,

01:32.926 --> 01:34.227
and your little baby too.

01:34.294 --> 01:36.229
- Bobo's no baby!

01:36.296 --> 01:38.031
He's a monster.

01:38.097 --> 01:41.167
Yes, aren't you
my little monster?

01:41.234 --> 01:43.369
Yes, you are!

01:43.436 --> 01:46.606
And it isn't a club.
It's a gang.

01:46.673 --> 01:48.575
The Devilled Eggs.

01:48.641 --> 01:50.610
- That's so cool!
[Bobo whimpers]

01:50.677 --> 01:51.911
Oh, hi there.

01:51.978 --> 01:53.980
- I want Harvey to join
The Devilled Eggs too.

01:54.047 --> 01:58.251
- This little cream puff's
way too soft for gang life.

01:58.318 --> 01:59.919
- Hey!
I'm tough!

01:59.986 --> 02:01.254
I'll prove it.

02:01.321 --> 02:03.923
Would a cream puff dance
like this?

02:03.990 --> 02:06.926
<i>[orchestral pop music plays]</i>

02:06.993 --> 02:12.899
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:12.966 --> 02:16.035
{\an3}- Harvey's cool, Blister.
Look, I know this guy.

02:16.102 --> 02:18.304
{\an3}He's totally
Devilled Eggs material.

02:18.371 --> 02:19.772
Just give him a chance.

02:19.839 --> 02:21.841
- All right, fine.

02:21.908 --> 02:23.176
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:23.243 --> 02:24.611
<i>[music stops]</i>
- Wow!

02:24.677 --> 02:26.346
A Devilled Eggs jacket?

02:26.412 --> 02:28.214
But where's the patch?

02:28.281 --> 02:32.886
{\an1}- You gotta pass initiation
first, and it ain't easy.

02:32.952 --> 02:35.955
- You got this, dude.
- I won't let you down.

02:36.022 --> 02:37.957
I'm gonna prove how tough I am.

02:38.024 --> 02:39.659
[giggles]

02:39.726 --> 02:42.161
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

02:42.228 --> 02:45.932
- Okay, this is
your first task, bub.

02:45.999 --> 02:48.468
You see that fire alarm
over there?

02:48.535 --> 02:49.636
- I sure do.

02:49.702 --> 02:52.071
- You gotta set it off.

02:52.138 --> 02:54.440
Send all these dorks runnin'.

02:54.507 --> 02:57.577
- You want me to pull the alarm
even though there's no fire?

02:57.644 --> 03:00.780
- I want this place empty.
You got that?

03:00.847 --> 03:03.149
- Hmm...
I think I'm pickin' up

03:03.216 --> 03:04.651
what you're puttin' down.

03:04.717 --> 03:06.419
I'm smellin'
what you're cookin'.

03:06.486 --> 03:08.121
I think I'm catchin'
what you're--

03:08.187 --> 03:09.389
- Just go do it!

03:09.455 --> 03:11.357
- Okay!

03:11.424 --> 03:13.326
- If he can pull this off,

03:13.393 --> 03:16.162
this place will erupt in chao--
<i>[static over intercom]</i>

03:16.229 --> 03:17.830
<i>- [on intercom]</i>
<i>Good morning, everyone.</i>

03:17.897 --> 03:20.533
<i>I hope you're having</i>
<i>a peaceful reading experience.</i>

03:20.600 --> 03:22.035
- Huh?
- This is your

03:22.101 --> 03:23.603
friendly neighborhood
Harvey Beaks,

03:23.670 --> 03:25.772
here to announce
a surprise fire drill.

03:25.838 --> 03:27.707
- What?
<i>- [on intercom] In a moment,</i>

03:27.774 --> 03:30.143
<i>our lovely librarian</i>
<i>will activate the alarm.</i>

03:30.209 --> 03:32.612
[alarm blares]
<i>Calmly bookmark your page,</i>

03:32.679 --> 03:35.281
<i>and leave through</i>
<i>the emergency exits.</i>

03:35.348 --> 03:37.750
We're sorry to interrupt
your reading adventures,

03:37.817 --> 03:41.588
but what's an adventure without
standard safety protocol?

03:41.654 --> 03:43.356
Thank you.
[alarm stops]

03:43.423 --> 03:45.124
- What the heck was that?

03:45.191 --> 03:46.526
- I completed the challenge.

03:46.593 --> 03:48.962
{\an3}- Well, he technically did
what you said.

03:49.028 --> 03:50.396
The place is empty.

03:50.463 --> 03:53.366
- [grumbling]
Huh, yeah, I guess so.

03:53.433 --> 03:55.368
All right, kid, not bad.

03:55.435 --> 03:58.504
{\an3}But the next test
ain't so easy.

03:58.571 --> 04:04.310
You gotta survive a ride down
Dead Man's Hill.

04:04.377 --> 04:06.980
- Sure does seem...deadly.

04:07.046 --> 04:09.616
- It's covered in sharp turns,

04:09.682 --> 04:14.020
50-foot drops,
and some of it is just on fire!

04:14.087 --> 04:17.490
I don't know why,
but it's stinkin' sweet!

04:17.557 --> 04:20.093
Only the toughest
of the tough can--

04:20.159 --> 04:22.829
{\an1}- Hey, sorry.
Could you repeat that?

04:22.895 --> 04:24.797
I got a bit preoccupied.

04:24.864 --> 04:26.933
- Oh, uh, sure.

04:27.000 --> 04:30.303
Dead Man's Hill is covered in...

04:30.370 --> 04:32.839
sharp...turns,

04:32.905 --> 04:35.341
50-foot...drops,

04:35.408 --> 04:38.978
and...
a butterfly garden?

04:39.045 --> 04:40.680
What the heck happened?

04:40.747 --> 04:43.549
- I organized a community effort
to renovate the park.

04:43.616 --> 04:45.284
Now it's not so scary.

04:45.351 --> 04:47.920
Anyways, I gotta complete
my trial.

04:47.987 --> 04:49.555
Weeee!

04:49.622 --> 04:53.459
- He took something scary
and made it beautiful.

04:53.526 --> 04:55.895
- [grumbles]
- Aw, come on, Blister.

04:55.962 --> 04:58.364
<i>I know Harvey's got a weird way</i>
<i>of doing things,</i>

04:58.431 --> 05:00.433
<i>and, sure,</i>
<i>he's a bit of a dork,</i>

05:00.500 --> 05:02.035
<i>but he's still super cool.</i>

05:02.101 --> 05:03.703
He's totally gang material.

05:03.770 --> 05:06.906
- Well, I'll admit,
the kid is impressive.

05:06.973 --> 05:10.276
And he's finding his way through
all my tests.

05:10.343 --> 05:13.746
I mean, this place does look
incredi--

05:13.813 --> 05:15.715
oh, my heck.

05:15.782 --> 05:17.884
- Whew!
What a lovely ride.

05:17.950 --> 05:20.953
{\an3}- All right, kid,
you've earned my respect.

05:21.020 --> 05:23.690
- Does this mean I get my patch?
- Not yet.

05:23.756 --> 05:25.625
You still have one more test.

05:25.692 --> 05:29.862
But I have decided
to give you a nickname.

05:29.929 --> 05:31.297
Baby Teeth.

05:31.364 --> 05:32.999
- Is that some kind of metaphor

05:33.066 --> 05:35.001
about how even though
I'm little right now,

05:35.068 --> 05:37.003
I have a lot of potential
and room to grow?

05:37.070 --> 05:40.573
- No, it's just 'cause
your mouth is so tiny.

05:40.640 --> 05:43.209
Seriously, it's so small.

05:43.276 --> 05:45.144
{\an3}Like, wow.

05:45.211 --> 05:47.246
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:47.313 --> 05:49.048
Okay, Baby Teeth, listen up.

05:49.115 --> 05:54.120
This is the home base for our
rival gang, The Hip Bones.

05:54.187 --> 05:56.956
- Rival gang?
This plot's getting so thick,

05:57.023 --> 05:58.458
you could spread it on toast.

05:58.524 --> 06:01.160
- Now, your task is to sneak in

06:01.227 --> 06:04.731
and put this little shirt
on their gang mascot.

06:04.797 --> 06:06.866
It says, "Yolk's On You!"

06:06.933 --> 06:09.802
You pass this test,
you get your patch.

06:09.869 --> 06:11.504
Good luck!

06:11.571 --> 06:13.339
- Thank you for believing in me!

06:13.406 --> 06:15.374
[grunts]
Okay.

06:15.441 --> 06:18.344
Now to find the evil gang
in this...

06:18.411 --> 06:20.747
lovely...home?

06:20.813 --> 06:22.215
Cookies?

06:22.281 --> 06:24.417
Floral arrangements?

06:24.484 --> 06:27.019
Knitting and kindness?

06:27.086 --> 06:29.021
This place is full of sweeties.

06:29.088 --> 06:30.957
Hmm.
Oh!

06:31.023 --> 06:33.359
Is that the mascot?

06:33.426 --> 06:35.361
Is this even a gang?

06:35.428 --> 06:38.431
Um, hi, excuse me, Miss.

06:38.498 --> 06:41.267
{\an1}- Oh, hello there,
little one.

06:41.334 --> 06:43.169
Please, call me Fuzzy.

06:43.236 --> 06:44.904
- Nice to meet you, Fuzzy.

06:44.971 --> 06:47.006
So, I was wondering,

06:47.073 --> 06:50.643
you're not part
of some dastardly gang, right?

06:50.710 --> 06:53.346
- A gang?
Oh, heavens no.

06:53.412 --> 06:55.214
We're all quite wholesome here.

06:55.281 --> 06:57.683
{\an3}- I'm so sorry,
it's just I've been auditioning

06:57.750 --> 06:59.652
{\an3}for a part in this gang,
The Devilled Eggs,

06:59.719 --> 07:01.921
{\an3}and I'm supposed to prank you,
but you're so sweet.

07:01.988 --> 07:04.323
{\an3}My baby teeth are never gonna
grow up into big kid teeth

07:04.390 --> 07:05.958
{\an3}and I'll never be a--
[panting]

07:06.025 --> 07:08.795
{\an1}- Aw, aren't you just a sad,
little nugget?

07:08.861 --> 07:12.698
{\an1}I'm sure this is just
a big ol' misunderstanding.

07:12.765 --> 07:15.368
{\an1}Now, how about me
and a few of the folks here

07:15.434 --> 07:17.870
{\an1}take you back
to your little clubhouse?

07:17.937 --> 07:19.205
- Um, sure.

07:19.272 --> 07:20.873
That'd be great.

07:20.940 --> 07:24.343
[door opens]
Okay, here's the secret hideout!

07:24.410 --> 07:26.846
- [gasps]
- Hey, Blister!

07:26.913 --> 07:28.114
This is Fuzzy.

07:28.181 --> 07:29.982
- Oh...
[laughs]

07:30.049 --> 07:32.285
Looks like I finally found

07:32.351 --> 07:34.887
your secret hideout, Blister.

07:34.954 --> 07:37.456
- Wait. What?
- Get 'em, gang!

07:37.523 --> 07:39.692
Fire the crochet net, Blanche!

07:39.759 --> 07:42.228
- No!
We're trapped!

07:42.295 --> 07:44.797
But it's so comfy.
- Gang?

07:44.864 --> 07:47.033
I thought you were a sweet,
old lady.

07:47.099 --> 07:48.434
You're bad?

07:48.501 --> 07:51.070
- I'm bad to the hip bone, kid.

07:51.137 --> 07:52.438
{\an3}Get it?

07:52.505 --> 07:53.806
Tear this place up.

07:53.873 --> 07:55.341
[both shout]

07:55.408 --> 07:57.810
- [stammers and gasps]

07:57.877 --> 07:59.579
[thermostat beeps
and air whooshes]

07:59.645 --> 08:01.714
- [gasps]
[Bobo barks]

08:01.781 --> 08:04.550
- [gasps]
No! Bobo!

08:04.617 --> 08:07.119
[barks and whimpers]

08:07.186 --> 08:09.422
{\an3}- [laughs]

08:09.488 --> 08:12.291
Who's the yolk on now, Blister?

08:12.358 --> 08:14.427
Later, eggheads!

08:14.493 --> 08:17.496
Oh, and thanks again, kid.

08:17.563 --> 08:19.799
{\an3}Couldn't have done it
without you.

08:19.866 --> 08:21.200
{\an3}[laughs]

08:21.267 --> 08:22.335
- Oh, no!
[door closes]

08:22.401 --> 08:24.804
[all groaning]

08:24.871 --> 08:26.305
- Oh, Bobo!

08:26.372 --> 08:28.074
My sweet Bobo!

08:28.140 --> 08:29.942
Our gang is ruined!

08:30.009 --> 08:31.444
- This is all my fault.

08:31.510 --> 08:34.080
I guess there's no devil
in my egg.

08:34.145 --> 08:36.048
I'll see myself out.

08:39.518 --> 08:40.620
- Harvey, wait!

08:40.686 --> 08:42.087
- Don't look at me.

08:42.154 --> 08:44.290
I'm just a sad,
little cream puff,

08:44.357 --> 08:47.360
not even tough enough
to put a T-shirt on a pet.

08:47.426 --> 08:48.828
- Dude, listen.

08:48.895 --> 08:51.230
{\an1}You are your own brand
of tough.

08:51.297 --> 08:52.698
That's what makes you special.

08:52.765 --> 08:55.134
- You're just saying that.
- I mean it, man.

08:55.201 --> 08:57.603
You're super tough on germs
and stuff,

08:57.670 --> 08:59.505
and, like, you never give up,

08:59.572 --> 09:01.440
no matter how hard
you gotta scrub.

09:01.507 --> 09:02.608
- Yeah!

09:02.675 --> 09:05.111
I am hard-core with a sponge.

09:05.177 --> 09:09.248
Hmm...
Hmm!

09:09.315 --> 09:10.449
- [laughs]

09:10.516 --> 09:11.784
[doorbell rings]

09:11.851 --> 09:13.786
Now, who the heck could that be?

09:13.853 --> 09:15.521
Hello?

09:15.588 --> 09:18.324
[gasps]
Hot-diggity-dog!

09:18.391 --> 09:21.727
A third little baby just for me.

09:22.628 --> 09:24.597
Look at all of you.

09:24.664 --> 09:26.766
You're so cute!

09:26.832 --> 09:29.869
Now, hold tight.
I'ma get you some treats.

09:29.936 --> 09:31.570
- Hey.
[Bobo and Cupcake whimper]

09:31.637 --> 09:34.640
- I found this big ol' bag
of cookies.

09:34.707 --> 09:36.342
Wanna split it with me?

09:36.409 --> 09:37.810
<i>[dramatic musical sting]</i>

09:37.877 --> 09:39.111
Babies?

09:39.178 --> 09:40.846
Where are you, sweeties?

09:40.913 --> 09:42.515
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:42.581 --> 09:45.184
What?

09:45.251 --> 09:47.420
Well, this is the place.

09:47.486 --> 09:49.255
- There you are!

09:49.322 --> 09:51.791
Give me back my Bobo!

09:51.857 --> 09:54.260
He needs his medication!

09:54.327 --> 09:56.395
- You give me back my Cupcake!

09:56.462 --> 09:58.798
I got your stupid note,
you old geezer!

09:58.864 --> 10:01.934
- I got your stupid note!

10:02.001 --> 10:05.871
- Ladies and gentlemen,
I wrote those stupid notes!

10:05.938 --> 10:07.673
[all gasp]
Yeah!

10:07.740 --> 10:09.375
I got your little buggies,

10:09.442 --> 10:11.577
and the only way you're ever
gonna see 'em again

10:11.644 --> 10:13.245
is if you do what I say.

10:13.312 --> 10:15.081
- Tell us your demands.

10:15.147 --> 10:18.617
- I demand you...

10:18.684 --> 10:20.486
kiss and make up.

10:20.553 --> 10:22.221
- What?
- Heck no!

10:22.288 --> 10:23.356
- Do it!

10:23.422 --> 10:26.859
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:26.926 --> 10:27.994
Hey!

10:28.060 --> 10:29.829
Do it tender!

10:31.664 --> 10:33.666
[both grumbling]

10:33.733 --> 10:34.934
That's better.

10:35.001 --> 10:37.069
Okay, a deal's a deal.

10:37.136 --> 10:39.505
They were a little dirty,
so I gave them a bath.

10:39.572 --> 10:41.340
[Cupcake barks]
Hope you don't mind.

10:41.407 --> 10:43.509
[both gasp]
both: Ooh!

10:43.576 --> 10:46.679
[overlapping chatter]

10:46.746 --> 10:47.847
<i>[bell tings]</i>

10:47.913 --> 10:50.783
- Kid, I was wrong about you.

10:50.850 --> 10:53.753
You may not be tough
in the traditional sense,

10:53.819 --> 10:56.522
but unifying enemies like this,
well...

10:56.589 --> 10:59.058
I'd say that's pretty punk.

10:59.125 --> 11:01.994
Here's your patch, Baby Teeth.

11:02.061 --> 11:04.196
Glad to have you.

11:04.263 --> 11:05.598
- I'm a Devilled Egg!

11:05.664 --> 11:08.501
Thank you so much for letting me
join your company, sir!

11:08.567 --> 11:09.735
- It's not a company.

11:09.802 --> 11:13.439
{\an1}It's a--
oh, whatever.

11:13.506 --> 11:14.640
<i>[bell tings]</i>

11:16.642 --> 11:19.578
<i>[whimsical music]</i>

11:19.645 --> 11:26.786
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:31.690 --> 11:33.893
{\an1}- [sighs]
Aah!

11:33.959 --> 11:35.094
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:35.161 --> 11:36.829
[both grunt]
- Oh, excuse me!

11:36.896 --> 11:38.330
After you.
- Oh, oh, no.

11:38.397 --> 11:40.232
After you.
- No, no, after you.

11:40.299 --> 11:42.468
- After you.
- Excuse me, fellas.

11:42.535 --> 11:43.769
both: After you!

11:43.836 --> 11:50.342
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:50.409 --> 11:52.511
- [gasps] My hummus!
[container thuds on ground]

11:52.578 --> 11:59.518
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:00.686 --> 12:02.555
Oh, cool!

12:02.621 --> 12:05.558
<i>[rousing music]</i>

12:05.624 --> 12:12.565
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:13.632 --> 12:15.501
So I found a fence.

12:15.568 --> 12:16.735
both: Wow!

12:16.802 --> 12:17.903
- What should we name it?

12:17.970 --> 12:19.605
- I'm gonna call him "Harvey."

12:19.672 --> 12:21.006
- That's just confusing.

12:21.073 --> 12:22.575
- We can call it
whatever we want.

12:22.641 --> 12:24.844
With a little fresh paint,
it'll be something

12:24.910 --> 12:26.512
all of Littlebark can enjoy.

12:26.579 --> 12:29.115
- People will come from all over
to jump over it,

12:29.181 --> 12:30.649
climb it, walk around it.

12:30.716 --> 12:33.119
There's about a million ways
to have fun here.

12:33.185 --> 12:36.021
- I'm having fun already!

12:36.088 --> 12:37.690
- One thing is for sure.

12:37.756 --> 12:39.592
{\an3}This is gonna be
the best white fence

12:39.658 --> 12:40.960
anyone has ever seen.

12:41.026 --> 12:43.262
- Wait!
- Huh?

12:43.329 --> 12:46.298
{\an1}- Uh, I hope you're not planning
on painting that fence white.

12:46.365 --> 12:49.101
Don't you think it would
look better as a yellow fence?

12:49.168 --> 12:51.904
A nice, golden yellow.

12:51.971 --> 12:54.106
- I guess yellow's fine with me.

12:54.173 --> 12:55.674
Is that okay with you guys?

12:55.741 --> 12:57.576
- We don't care.
- Okay.

12:57.643 --> 12:58.611
Yellow it is.

12:58.677 --> 13:00.880
- [munching and grumbling]

13:00.946 --> 13:03.082
This icing tastes terrible!

13:04.817 --> 13:06.318
What's that?
- Oh...

13:06.385 --> 13:08.921
{\an1}well, we're just about to paint
this fence.

13:08.988 --> 13:11.390
{\an3}- I think it should be pink,
like me.

13:11.457 --> 13:13.492
{\an1}- Uh, hold on a second there,
Princess.

13:13.559 --> 13:16.462
{\an1}Don't you think a pink fence
would be a bit garish?

13:16.529 --> 13:19.932
{\an1}I mean, yellow is such a nice,
inoffensive color.

13:19.999 --> 13:22.668
- Yeah, right!
Pink is high-class and awesome.

13:22.735 --> 13:25.204
Yellow is something you put
in a toilet.

13:25.271 --> 13:27.173
{\an1}- Look, it's gotta be yellow,
and that's that.

13:27.239 --> 13:29.008
{\an3}- Ew!
Pink is way cuter!

13:29.074 --> 13:31.410
- Yellow! Yellow!
- Pink!

13:31.477 --> 13:33.112
{\an3}- What are you gonna do
about this, Harvey?

13:33.179 --> 13:36.415
- Yeah!
- Uh...

13:36.482 --> 13:38.384
I know!

13:38.450 --> 13:41.554
<i>So, thank you all for coming</i>
<i>to this community assembly.</i>

13:41.620 --> 13:43.322
I'd like to give
a special shout-out

13:43.389 --> 13:47.226
to my mom's marshmallows bars
for being so delicious.

13:47.293 --> 13:50.496
- Good luck with your
political movement, sweetie!

13:50.563 --> 13:51.964
- I love you, Mommy!

13:52.031 --> 13:55.067
I'd also like to give a special
shout-out to Bartleburt

13:55.134 --> 13:57.636
for letting me use
this library rec room.

13:57.703 --> 14:00.039
I love you, Bartleburt!

14:00.105 --> 14:01.640
About the fence.

14:01.707 --> 14:03.475
It's old, unsightly,

14:03.542 --> 14:05.511
and we're going to do something
about it.

14:05.578 --> 14:08.180
- Well, some people like big,
ugly eyesores,

14:08.247 --> 14:09.815
like my son Randl.

14:09.882 --> 14:11.317
He'll be loved someday.

14:11.383 --> 14:13.819
- So in an effort
to keep Littlebark beautiful,

14:13.886 --> 14:16.789
we're going to vote on
what color to paint the fence.

14:16.855 --> 14:18.390
It's called democracy.

14:18.457 --> 14:22.228
- Sounds like something fake
invented by the government!

14:23.796 --> 14:25.531
- Right.

14:25.598 --> 14:28.100
So, we're gonna hear
a couple arguments.

14:28.167 --> 14:29.702
If we could just talk
one at a time--

14:29.768 --> 14:31.070
- Let me handle this, Harvey.

14:31.136 --> 14:32.871
The last thing Littlebark needs

14:32.938 --> 14:35.407
is another monument to oddballs.

14:35.474 --> 14:39.578
Allow me to tell you about
a little color called yellow.

14:39.645 --> 14:42.915
Yellow, a color of tradition
in our community.

14:42.982 --> 14:46.919
It's a color of family
and a color of togetherness.

14:46.986 --> 14:51.223
Yellow is--
well, it's just what's right.

14:51.290 --> 14:52.858
<i>[chimes tinkling]</i>
And also,

14:52.925 --> 14:55.160
pink will cause
the downfall of society!

14:55.227 --> 14:57.529
Like this perfectly good
vanilla ice cream!

14:57.596 --> 15:00.099
It's been ruined by chunks
of pink berries!

15:00.165 --> 15:01.934
Fear it!
Fear the pink!

15:02.001 --> 15:04.203
[all screaming]

15:04.270 --> 15:06.505
- Ah! Ah!
- Thank you for your time,

15:06.572 --> 15:11.377
and may the color yellow bless
each and every one of--aah!

15:13.579 --> 15:15.881
- Ever since yesterday,
my main goal in life

15:15.948 --> 15:19.652
is to paint the fence pink,
and this will explain why.

15:19.718 --> 15:22.187
<i>[hip-hop music plays]</i>

15:22.254 --> 15:25.057
[beeping]
<i>♪ Hot and pink ♪</i>

15:25.124 --> 15:28.060
<i>[staccato vocalizing]</i>

15:28.127 --> 15:31.030
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:31.096 --> 15:33.599
<i>♪ Hot hot hot hot</i>
<i>hot hot hot hot ♪</i>

15:33.666 --> 15:36.168
<i>♪ Yeah pink ♪</i>
<i>[music stops]</i>

15:36.235 --> 15:38.437
- Hmm, yeah,
I could blindly follow that.

15:38.504 --> 15:40.439
- So, basically,
the fence should be pink,

15:40.506 --> 15:43.142
and anyone who disagrees with me
can go straight to--

15:43.208 --> 15:44.843
- Okay!
- [groans]

15:44.910 --> 15:47.279
- So, now that we've heard
from both sides,

15:47.346 --> 15:49.381
in addition to the literature
on paint samples

15:49.448 --> 15:52.117
we distributed earlier,
you should all now

15:52.184 --> 15:54.253
be well informed enough to vote.

15:54.320 --> 15:55.988
- [whimpering]
- [snoring]

15:56.055 --> 15:58.390
- Make sure your voice is heard.

15:58.457 --> 16:00.025
Once you've filled out
your ballot,

16:00.092 --> 16:01.660
please drop them
into the ballot box

16:01.727 --> 16:04.196
handled by our
lovely volunteers.

16:04.263 --> 16:06.031
We will announce
the election results

16:06.098 --> 16:07.333
at the fence tomorrow.

16:07.399 --> 16:09.868
Thank you for your time
and patience.

16:09.935 --> 16:11.070
See you tomorrow.

16:11.136 --> 16:12.538
Well, it's tomorrow,

16:12.604 --> 16:14.273
and we're all here at the fence.

16:14.340 --> 16:17.609
And, as promised,
the results of the election.

16:17.676 --> 16:22.114
Foo, Fee, tell us if the fence
will be yellow or pink!

16:22.181 --> 16:24.083
- Neither!
- Huh?

16:24.149 --> 16:26.118
- The votes are tied.
- Yup.

16:26.185 --> 16:28.354
Completely even.
- A tie?

16:28.420 --> 16:30.956
- I didn't go getting out of bed
before noon for this!

16:31.023 --> 16:34.493
- 35, 45...wait!

16:34.560 --> 16:36.495
Someone didn't vote.

16:36.562 --> 16:38.831
- Uh...

16:38.897 --> 16:41.433
{\an3}- Kratz, we've always
been friends.

16:41.500 --> 16:44.169
{\an3}And you wouldn't let
your friend lose, would you?

16:44.236 --> 16:45.838
- You don't even
have to like me!

16:45.904 --> 16:48.240
Just vote pink already!

16:48.307 --> 16:50.109
- Come on, Kratz.

16:50.175 --> 16:51.910
Do your civic duty.

16:51.977 --> 16:54.847
{\an3}- [sighs]
Okay.

16:54.913 --> 16:59.718
- And the final
tie-breaking vote is for...

16:59.785 --> 17:00.853
green?

17:00.919 --> 17:02.454
- Oh, a free thinker!

17:02.521 --> 17:05.324
An individualist!
- Sorry.

17:05.391 --> 17:07.593
- Now, now, now,
in democracy,

17:07.659 --> 17:09.928
even the useless votes
are counted.

17:09.994 --> 17:12.664
[wind whooshes]

17:12.731 --> 17:15.300
- Well, obviously democracy
is broken!

17:15.367 --> 17:16.902
- Is this the fall of society?

17:16.969 --> 17:19.538
Do we just start jabbing
each other with sticks now?

17:19.605 --> 17:21.073
- All right,
I'll take a thousand bucks

17:21.140 --> 17:22.808
for half a tank of gasoline!

17:22.875 --> 17:25.210
- Bring on the apocalypse!

17:25.277 --> 17:27.913
[overlapping arguing]

17:27.980 --> 17:29.748
- Everyone!
Calm down!

17:29.815 --> 17:31.984
Just go home
and come back tomorrow.

17:32.050 --> 17:35.788
I'll think of a way
to fix all of this, I promise.

17:35.854 --> 17:39.858
[overlapping agreements]

17:39.925 --> 17:42.861
<i>[quirky music]</i>

17:42.928 --> 17:48.267
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:50.002 --> 17:51.069
- All right.

17:51.136 --> 17:53.038
We're doing this for Littlebark.

17:53.105 --> 17:55.474
- You sure you don't want
to watch everyone fight?

17:55.541 --> 17:58.444
- No. I just want everyone
to be happy.

17:58.510 --> 18:00.345
You know what to do.

18:04.450 --> 18:06.318
- Anyway, it feels like
we were just here.

18:06.385 --> 18:08.220
Hm.
[all gasp]

18:08.287 --> 18:09.521
- Oh!
- What? What is it?

18:09.588 --> 18:11.390
I want to see!
[gasps]

18:11.457 --> 18:13.559
It's...it's...

18:13.625 --> 18:15.494
pink!

18:15.561 --> 18:18.897
- Remember, people, if anyone
tries to rationally debate you,

18:18.964 --> 18:20.732
you shout them down!

18:20.799 --> 18:21.767
[all gasp]

18:21.834 --> 18:23.368
A yellow fence?

18:23.435 --> 18:25.037
It's a gosh-darn miracle!

18:25.103 --> 18:28.073
[overlapping happy chatter]

18:28.140 --> 18:29.274
- Just a second.
Wait.

18:29.341 --> 18:30.709
Why are you guys happy?

18:30.776 --> 18:34.246
- The fence is pink.
We won, you weirdos.

18:34.313 --> 18:37.115
Hey!
- What?

18:37.182 --> 18:39.117
- So, what do you guys think?

18:39.184 --> 18:40.586
Pretty great, huh?

18:40.652 --> 18:43.055
[overlapping angry screaming]

18:43.121 --> 18:44.623
It's called compromise.

18:44.690 --> 18:46.391
That way, everybody wins.

18:46.458 --> 18:47.826
- But it's not winning

18:47.893 --> 18:50.529
if the people who are wrong
don't lose!

18:50.596 --> 18:52.397
- Even knowing the other side
is yellow,

18:52.464 --> 18:54.299
I just--I'm gonna throw up.

18:54.366 --> 18:55.534
- Oh, yeah?

18:55.601 --> 18:57.269
Well, how do you feel
about this?

18:57.336 --> 18:58.637
[grunts]
- [gasps]

18:58.704 --> 18:59.738
- Ah!

18:59.805 --> 19:01.573
[growls]
Attack!

19:01.640 --> 19:03.342
- [screams]
- [grunts]

19:03.408 --> 19:07.112
[overlapping angry shouting]

19:07.179 --> 19:08.614
- What about our town spirit?

19:08.680 --> 19:10.649
Keeping Littlebark pretty?

19:10.716 --> 19:13.285
{\an1}- [gasps]
Harvey's dead!

19:13.352 --> 19:16.955
- I'm not dead, Foo,
democracy is.

19:17.022 --> 19:18.190
- Fire!

19:18.257 --> 19:20.125
<i>[rock music]</i>

19:20.192 --> 19:21.927
- Aah!
Oh!

19:21.994 --> 19:25.130
- The fence should be red!

19:25.197 --> 19:26.932
- The fence should be green!

19:26.999 --> 19:28.267
[grunts]

19:28.333 --> 19:31.103
- [laughs]

19:31.169 --> 19:32.471
- Whoa!

19:32.538 --> 19:34.873
{\an3}Harvey, this is really
getting out of hand.

19:34.940 --> 19:36.308
- We gotta do something.

19:36.375 --> 19:38.010
- What's the point
in doing anything?

19:38.076 --> 19:40.445
Everyone just wants
to keep fighting anyway.

19:40.512 --> 19:41.947
- You can't be sure of that.

19:42.014 --> 19:44.783
Let me check
if they're still fighting.

19:44.850 --> 19:47.719
Yup, they're still fighting.

19:47.786 --> 19:49.154
- [laughs]

19:49.221 --> 19:50.789
- [screams]

19:50.856 --> 19:52.691
[both grunt]

19:52.758 --> 19:55.327
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:55.394 --> 19:57.195
- Look out, suckers!

19:57.262 --> 20:02.768
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:02.834 --> 20:04.770
- This isn't what I wanted.

20:04.836 --> 20:07.940
I just wanted to make the fence
nice for everyone.

20:08.006 --> 20:10.776
<i>[gentle uplifting music]</i>

20:10.842 --> 20:12.277
[sighs]

20:12.344 --> 20:14.212
You know, it's weird.

20:14.279 --> 20:17.149
The fence looks so tiny
from up here.

20:17.215 --> 20:24.356
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:35.500 --> 20:38.637
<i>[rousing orchestral music]</i>

20:38.704 --> 20:40.172
{\an1}- Harvey?

20:40.238 --> 20:47.379
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:49.881 --> 20:52.317
- Stop!

20:52.384 --> 20:54.186
- Yo, man, what are you doing?

20:54.252 --> 20:56.188
- Why are you disrupting
our fight?

20:56.254 --> 21:00.926
What insightful thing could you
have to say right now?

21:00.993 --> 21:02.361
- I realized something.

21:02.427 --> 21:05.430
Littlebark is a beautiful town
full of beautiful people

21:05.497 --> 21:06.932
of many different colors.

21:06.999 --> 21:12.004
Yellow, pink, green,
and even purple.

21:12.070 --> 21:13.338
- Aww.

21:13.405 --> 21:15.240
- On one hand,
it doesn't matter

21:15.307 --> 21:18.043
what color we paint the fence,
but on the other,

21:18.110 --> 21:20.746
it's the most important decision
in the world

21:20.812 --> 21:22.981
because it represents us.

21:23.048 --> 21:26.351
So I say...there.

21:26.418 --> 21:28.920
This is how we paint it.

21:30.555 --> 21:31.723
- Okay, sure.

21:31.790 --> 21:33.225
- I guess that makes
enough sense.

21:33.291 --> 21:40.432
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:02.054 --> 22:04.990
<i>[cheerful music]</i>

22:05.057 --> 22:11.997
<i>♪ ♪</i>
